---
title: Herbs de Provence Chicken over a Warm Farro, Mozzarella, and Tomato Jumble
description: Between France’s bistro fare and Italy’s trattoria eats, it’s hard to say which country has the supreme cuisine. In fact, we love both so much that we’re tempted to make a hybrid out of the two and call it Fritalian. So say hello to our border-hopping recipe, which features both chicken seasoned with herbs de Provence (southern France’s trademark seasoning) and a farro caprese that is loaded with classic Italian ingredients, like tomatoes, mozzarella, and balsamic vinegar.
